[[collapsible show="ADDENDUM 6549/II - INTERCEPTED COMMUNICATION" hide="COLLAPSE"]]
@@ @@
[[div class="blockquote"]]
= [[span class="bt"]]RELEVANT COMMUNICATIONS LOG[[/span]]
----
[[span class="bt"]]DATE:[[/span]] 02/10/2023, 2:29 AM GMT-4.

[[span class="bt"]]NOTE:[[/span]] The exact breadth of inciting factors behind the decision to remove SCP-6549 from "Tides of Change" is not known. However, the morning after the firing reportedly took place, VKTM Public Relations liaison Mari MacPhaerson received a threatening phone call from a Foundation-monitored payphone near Halifax, Nova Scotia, which has provided some insight into the events of that day in particular. SCP-6549 is suspected to have been involved in this communication, which has been transcribed below. 
----

= {{[BEGIN LOG]}}

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] //<Groggily.>// Hello?

//<A wet, sloshing noise, followed by heavy breathing and chittering.>// 

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] Anyone there? //<Pauses.>// Goddamn Pranklings. Stop calling me! That curse was illegitimate and you know it--[[footnote]]Context unknown.[[/footnote]] 

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]]  //<Voice speaks in a high pitch, though the tone is gravely serious.>// Mari. It's me. We need to talk. 

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] //<Pauses.>// Phil--?

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]] //<Gurgling. The sounds of traffic can be heard.>// 

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] //<Sighs.>// You can't just call me at two-thirty in the morning whenever you'd like. We're no longer colleagues, and whatever relationship we had, business or //otherwise//, doesn't exist anymore--

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]] //<A wet sound akin to suction, accompanied by a cracking noise. Later inspection of the payphone found the receiver's casing had been partially crushed.>// Look, I know. I know you think I'm being unreasonable. Just... Hear me out, okay?

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] You //shattered a stagehand's femur// yesterday, I think anyone can see that's pretty unreasonable, yeah. I don't even have eyes and I can see that. 

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]] //<A loud bang.>// It's //not// unreasonable! How come the fucking narrator gets his own trailer, huh? A fucking Airstream! I deserve my own Airstream! I deserve an assistant. They //need// me! //You need me!// 

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] Well, the producers don't exactly agree, now do they? Plus, David's accommodations are non-corporeal, they're more figurative than literal; we just called his trailer an Airstream because //it is intangible//! The cost is a fraction, not even considering we don't pay him--

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]] It was //my// face on the poster, Mari. My talent that springboarded us to fame, //Mari//. What, do you think it was all because of that hack, Appleborough--

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] Attenborough. 

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]]  //I don't care what his name is!// I want a second chance. You need to talk to someone, or things could get out of hand. //<Loud rustling.>//

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] The way you're behaving right now is part of the problem, Phil. //<Yawning.>// You're not Ryan Gosling, trying to pull off your magnum opus; you're an uncredited ancestral arthropod in the B plot of a nature documentary with like five hundred weekly viewers. Frankly, one of the worst-performing VKTM programs in recent history--

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]] //<Dryly.>// What did you just say?

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] Oh, come on, you should know that documentaries aren't the most popular of content these days--

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]] No-- Did you just say I'm the fucking //B plot// of 'Tides of Change'?

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] //One of the characters from the B plot.//  

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]] But- I thought--

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] Phil, have you watched an episode of the show? Like, //at all?//

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]] //<Indistinct splashing.>// Yeah, I skimmed them. The documentary parts are boring. Besides, I've been busy. Preparing for each shoot. Memorizing my lines--

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] //You don't have any lines, Phil!//

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]] Oh, I see what's going on here. This is all Tony's fuckin' fault. That bean counter probably gave us so little budget, knowing we'd blow it all on the nice stock footage and that old codger, so there wouldn't be enough left over for my amenities, right? He was always jealous of me, trying to undermine my career...

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] What 'career'? You're being ridiculous. You need to move on. From the project, and from-- //this.//

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]]  You- You think //I-// should- //<A pause, followed by a deep breath. The voice becomes unusually calm.>// You know what, you're right, Mari. You're always right.

[[span class="bt"]]MACPHAERSON:[[/span]] I am, yes. I'm going back to bed now. Good night, Phil.

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]] Good night. I'm sorry--

//<MacPhaerson hangs up the call on her end.>//

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]] --//Sorry that I'm not sorry! Not sorry!// You glorified fucking primate. //<Mockingly.>// 'Oh, look at me, I can walk upright! I've got phalanges that evolved to grip tools and stabilize me while I //sleep in a fucking tree like a fucking idiot!//' Evolved. Please. //<Pauses.>// We'll see about that, won't we?

[[span class="bt"]]PAYPHONE:[[/span]] //If you'd like to make a call, please hang up and try again. If you need help, please hang up and dial your operator. Thank you!//

[[span class="bt"]]UNKNOWN:[[/span]] //<Loudly.>// //[[span class="bt"]]FUCK YOU AND YOUR WHOLE SPECIES![[/span]]//

//<Individiual is heard grunting, followed by multiple loud impacts as the phone is presumably thrown at its cradle in an attempt to hang up the call. Communication ceases shortly thereafter.>//


= {{[END LOG]}}
[[/div]]
[[/collapsible]]
[[/=]]
@@ @@
[[=]]
[[collapsible show="ADDENDUM 6549/III - INTAKE TRANSCRIPT " hide="COLLAPSE"]]
@@ @@
[[div class="blockquote"]]
= [[span class="bt"]]SCP-6549 INITIAL INTAKE TRANSCRIPT[[/span]]
----
[[span class="bt"]]DATE:[[/span]] 06/23/2023

[[span class="bt"]]NOTE:[[/span]] SCP-6549 was obtained by the Foundation upon its arrest earlier that day. The following is a brief transcript of the initial interview between SCP-6549 and the Assistant Director of Site-184's Aquatic Anomalies Department, Elise BeauchÃªne, with a member of security personnel present for a portion of the interaction.
----

= {{[BEGIN LOG]}}

//<Lavalier microphone switches on. BeauchÃªne is seen on CCTV, pulling out a chair and sitting down at the metal table in front of her, sighing absentmindedly. Approximately thirty seconds later, there's a knock on the chamber door.>//

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] //Mouais.// You can come in. Leave it on the table.

//<A member of security personnel is enters, grunting as a heavy object is placed on the hard surface.>//

[[span class="bt"]]PERSONNEL:[[/span]] Back up. //<A pause, followed by the sound of scraping as BeauchÃªne is seen pushing her chair back with her legs.>// Good enough. First, I advise against opening the container yourself. Get like, three more people in here. Make sure you're all padded up, 'cause this thing nearly got us a few times on recovery. Second thing--

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] Wait, 'got you', how, exactly?

[[span class="bt"]]PERSONNEL:[[/span]]  Look, just don't say I didn't warn you. This thing is not the hermit crab your mother buys you from the boardwalk. //<Pauses.>// With all due respect. 

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] You didn't answer my question.

[[span class="bt"]]PERSONNEL:[[/span]] Well, we--

//<The container is heard moving as a loud, muffled bang emanates from within.>//

[[span class="bt"]]PERSONNEL:[[/span]] //<Clears throat.>// We don't really know. At least, we disagree on what we saw. //I'm// certain it was trying to impale us with one of those spindly legs it has, while Higgins swears he saw it pull a switchblade--

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] A //switchblade//? 

[[span class="bt"]]PERSONNEL:[[/span]] I said the same thing, but it's way more plausible if you've read the reports. You did read the reports, right? That was the second thing. 

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] No, I only just learned we were getting an angry, five-hundred-million-year-old shrimp the size of a small dog, like, half an hour ago? I've been getting the containment area set up, not much time to brief myself on this, I'm afraid.

[[span class="bt"]]PERSONNEL:[[/span]] Got it. Well, the international intelligence community has been tracking a string of murders, clear crimes of passion. The last few had the same MO; Bullet hole through the head, point blank, aiming downward, you know. Assassination-style, real clean. Now, unbeknownst to the authorities, all the victims were connected via association with VKTM. 

[[span class="bt"]]PERSONNEL:[[/span]] //<Indicating towards contrainer.>// This thing here had a strong argument against it for motive, as you'll read. Disgraced VKTM actor with unchecked anger issues who got the axe for being a diva and attacking staff in a fit of rage. Yet, every death involved was impossible for a creature of this nature. Not without some anomalous ability yet to be observed. Our measurements and diagnostics came back nominal.  

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] Bizarre. 

[[span class="bt"]]PERSONNEL:[[/span]] Oh, it gets weirder. Earlier today, local police in Anaheim found this bad boy while responding to reports of gunshots. It was just sitting there next to the corpse of an, uh, executive producer of some documentary series. They also found a gun lying nearby, in a puddle of seawater. Forensics confirmed it was the murder weapon, despite the obvious lack of thumbs, so our little friend here seems to have gotten sloppy.

//<Container shakes violently, followed by loud gurgling.>//

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] //Qu'est-ce que c'est?!// Sounds like distilled anger being strained through cheese cloth. How often does it make those //godawful// noises?

[[span class="bt"]]PERSONNEL:[[/span]] All the time. Constantly. Some are saying it should be able to speak English, but the thing hasn't said a word since police picked it up. Maybe it thinks keeping quiet will somehow be of help to it in the long run. Maybe it gets an interpreter, who knows. //<Raps knuckles on the solid steel of the box, contents responding with more aggression.>//

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] //<Sighs.>// Well, I'm glad containment is up and running for this... //thing// already. I'll have an auto-feeder added in soon, so none of us have to go near it unless absolutely necessary. Maybe soundproof the chamber, too. Or is that too big a risk?

[[span class="bt"]]PERSONNEL:[[/span]] Do what you want, I'm heading back to the States. Just remember; I warned you. And read the dossier. 

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] Mhm. Bye now. 

[[span class="bt"]]PERSONNEL:[[/span]] See you.

//<Security personnel leaves the room. The box emits muffled snarls at the sound of the closing door swinging shut.>//

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] So, what to do with you...

//<Wet clicks and chitters. BeauchÃªne skims the briefing on her phone.>//

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] Hmph. I don't buy it. Not only do I think you can talk, I think it probably pains you not to. You're a celebrity, right? Don't celebrities let the fame get to their heads? They think everyone wants to hear them talk. That everything revolves around them. Then, they lose it all in a series of misguided, self-absorbed acts that benefit no one. 

//<Container rattles. A bang is heard, though the box is unaffected.>//

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] Am I close? Did I hit a nerve? You lost it all, including your relationships, I bet. 

//<A series of bangs are registered. CCTV shows the box is intact, albeit bent outwards in multiple spots.>//

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] Were you being a bit of a--

//<BeauchÃªne quietly leans close to the container.>//

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] //<Whispering.>// --//Selfish shellfish?//

[[span class="bt"]]SCP-6549:[[/span]] //<Screaming, box audibly moving from the raucous activity within.>// [[span class="bt"]]//YOU BITCH! YOU FUCKING DID IT NOW!//[[/span]] I'll kill you! Reducing my existence to a bad pun? You are going to regret having legs! Lemme out!

//<Entity continues to attack the inside of its container. It throws itself against the side with a large bang that knocks the box off the table and onto the concrete below. It hits the floor on one of the two hinges securing the release hatch, which dislodges one and bends the other.>//

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] //<Standing, tripping backwards over her jacket, which had fallen off the back of her chair in the commotion.>// Ow. I--Damn. I hate it when I'm right.  

//<SCP-6549 chuckles and pries the hatch open, floating out with ease, eyes glowing white.>//

[[span class="bt"]]SCP-6549:[[/span]] It's time for me to finally become the main character of this world. Then, they'll take me back. She'll have to take me back. 

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] //<Scrambling back further, away from SCP-6549, and the exit.>// You don't have to do this--

[[span class="bt"]]SCP-6549:[[/span]] Step one, //eliminate all competition, [[span class="bt"]]starting with you.[[/span]]//

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]]  No-! //<She braces herself, covering her face from the approaching barbs.>//

//<Silence. After a moment, BeauchÃªne lowers her hands to see SCP-6549 mesmerized by a flashing red light in the upper corner of the chamber.>//

[[span class="bt"]]SCP-6549:[[/span]] Wait, have we been recording this entire time?! I think I missed a cue. 

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]]  Y-yeah? Yes! This is a live broadcast. Why did you think we had our driver come pick you up specifically? You've been selected to be play the protagonist. This is your real rise to stardom.  

[[span class="bt"]]SCP-6549:[[/span]] //<Overjoyed gurgling.>// Some part of me always knew. And no B plots? 

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]]  Nope. This show doesn't need a B plot. Too much intrigue.

[[span class="bt"]]SCP-6549:[[/span]] //<Chitters>// Well, I'm in!

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]]  We've also anticipated your arrival and have set up personal quarters for your use. Since you will be working so closely with the project, you should stay on-site--er, on-set.

//<SCP-6549 looks away from the camera.>//

[[span class="bt"]]SCP-6549:[[/span]] Huh? My own trailer... It's finally happening... Thank you.

[[span class="bt"]]BEAUCHÃNE:[[/span]] Let's get you settled. 


//The remainder of conversation has been redacted from this document for brevity. SCP-6549 is generally more passive and cooperative when entertaining its delusions. Other applications for the use of this technique are being researched.//[[footnote]] Such as convincing it to partake in heists, spycraft, assassinations, exploratory efforts, and other tasks.[[/footnote]]

